<subSubSection pageId="827" pageNumber="828" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="827" pageNumber="828">
<pageBreakToken pageId="827" pageNumber="828" start="start">Diversity</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="827" pageNumber="828">
About 275 species primarily in tropical areas of the Neotropical, Oriental, and Afrotropical Regions (over 95 % of the world fauna) with a few elements found in the Nearctic (11 species) and Palaearctic (ten species in Asia) Regions. The species are arrayed in three subgenera: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1824" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="827" pageNumber="828" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="827" pageNumber="828">Calleida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.str. (about 175 species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Callidiola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="827" pageNumber="828" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="827" pageNumber="828">Callidiola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jeannel (60 species), and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Stenocallida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="827" pageNumber="828" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="827" pageNumber="828">Stenocallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jeannel (40 species), though some authors (e.g., Casale 2008) treat 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Callidiola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="827" pageNumber="828" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="827" pageNumber="828">Callidiola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Stenocallida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="827" pageNumber="828" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="827" pageNumber="828">Stenocallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as distinct genera.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
